d dynamic-access call sites for this class:\n./forge/prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md:23:- Maintain a one-to-one mapping between dynamic-access report classes and generated test class files.\n./forge/prompt_templates/dynamic_access/optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration.md:12:Full dynamic-access coverage report, all classes with uncovered call sites:\n./forge/prompt_templates/dynamic_access/optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration.md:17:- Keep coverage for each dynamic-access class in its own dedicated `{test_language_display_name}` test file under `src/test/{test_source_dir_name}` in `graalvm-reachability-metadata`.\n./forge/prompt_templates/dynamic_access/optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration.md:18:- Maintain a one-to-one mapping between dynamic-access report classes and generated test class files.\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:98:  [--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access] \\\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:123:- `--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access` keeps generated tests for dynamic-access workflows even if no dynamic-access call sites are covered.\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:407:### Dynamic-access iterative workflow\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:409:The `dynamic_access_iterative` workflow improves metadata accuracy by using the `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport` Gradle task to identify which dynamic-access call sites (reflection, JNI, resources, serialization) are not yet covered by the generated tests. Instead of generating tests blindly, the workflow iterates class-by-class, sending the agent targeted prompts with the exact uncovered call sites for each class. After each attempt, the report is regenerated and coverage deltas are computed to decide whether to retry the same class or move on.\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:415:Dynamic-access strategies can optionally download library source code, upstream tests, and/or documentation as read-only agent context. This is configured per strategy via the `source-context-types` parameter in `predefined_strategies.json`. Available types are `main`, `test`, and `documentation`. The artifacts are downloaded from URLs in the library's `index.json` (populated by the `populateArtifactURLs` Gradle task) and extracted to `local_repositories/source_context/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/`.\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:440:Composite strategies (run a primary workflow, then refine dynamic-access coverage):\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:447:#### Running a dynamic-access strategy\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:469:For the detailed function-level notes and sequence diagram, see `docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md`.\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/increase_dynamic_access_coverage_strategy.py:12:    \"\"\"Composite strategy that runs a primary workflow then improves dynamic-access coverage.\"\"\"\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/increase_dynamic_access_coverage_strategy.py:35:            self._print_message(\"no primary workflow configured, skipping to dynamic-access coverage phase\")\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/increase_dynamic_access_coverage_strategy.py:46:                self._print_message(\"skipping dynamic-access coverage phase because primary workflow did not succeed\")\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/increase_dynamic_access_coverage_strategy.py:52:        self._print_message(\"starting dynamic-access coverage phase\")\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/increase_dynamic_access_coverage_strategy.py:61:            \"dynamic-access coverage phase completed with phase_ok={phase_ok}, iterations_added={iterations}\".format(\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/increase_dynamic_access_coverage_strategy.py:68:            self._print_message(\"keeping primary workflow result because dynamic-access coverage phase did not succeed\")\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.py:20:    \"\"\"Bulk dynamic-access coverage strategy that shows the full report to the agent.\"\"\"\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.py:2