vac`) failure** raised by a library version bump ([`fix_javac_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_javac_fail.py)); (3) **fix a JVM-mode (`javaTest`) runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_java_run_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_java_run_fail.py)); (4) **fix a `native-image` runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_ni_run.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_ni_run.py)); (5) **improve dynamic-access coverage** of already-supported libraries by targeting uncovered call sites; (6) **post-generation repair** of the metadata produced by a previous run ([`fix_post_generation_pi.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_post_generation_pi.py), [`fix_metadata_codex.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_metadata_codex.py)). Each task runs Gradle tasks against a worktree of this repo, appends a schema-validated metrics record, and — when invoked through [`forge/git_scripts/make_pr_*.py`](../forge/git_scripts/) — opens a PR for human review. See [forge/docs/architecture.md](../forge/docs/architecture.md). |\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:46:- A `stats/<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/stats.json` mirror of per-version metrics (dynamic-access call sites, coverage, lines of code, dependency information).\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:55:- Coverage collection (JaCoCo) and dynamic-access reporting per coordinate.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:74:- `latest/badges.json` — badges shown in the README (libraries supported, tested versions, dynamic-access coverage, tested LOC).\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:84:1. **Add new library support** — generate a JUnit test suite, scaffold metadata, iterate until JVM-mode tests pass and dynamic-access metadata is collected.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:87:4. **Improve coverage** of already-supported libraries by targeting uncovered dynamic-access call sites.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:191:- **FR-T-7** Dynamic-access coverage between consecutive tested versions of a library must not regress (enforced by reviewer skills `review-fixes-javac-fail`, `review-fixes-native-image-run-fail`, `review-fixes-java-run-fail`).\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:329:  Output: `metadata/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/test/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/AbstractLibraryStatsTask.java:197:                .resolve(\"dynamic-access\");\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/AbstractLibraryStatsTask.java:204:                .resolve(\"dynamic-access\")\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/AbstractLibraryStatsTask.java:205:                .resolve(\"dynamic-access-coverage.json\");\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/GenerateDynamicAccessCoverageReportTask.java:17: * Generates a per-class dynamic-access coverage report for matching coordinates.\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/GenerateDynamicAccessCoverageReportTask.java:20: * {@code metadata/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/test/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json}\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/GenerateDynamicAccessCoverageReportTask.java:70:            getLogger().quiet(\"Wrote dynamic-access coverage report for {} to {}.\", coordinate, outputFile);\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/GenerateDynamicAccessReportInvocationTask.java:19: * generated JSON files under `build/native/nativeTestCompile/dynamic-access`.\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/GenerateDynamicAccessReportInvocationTask.java:49:                .resolve(\"dynamic-access\");\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/AnalyzeExternalLibraryDynamicAccessTask.java:43: * Resolves an arbitrary Maven coordinate and computes dynamic-access totals without repo-tracked tests.