time failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_java_run_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_java_run_fail.py)); (4) **fix a `native-image` runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_ni_run.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_ni_run.py)); (5) **improve dynamic-access coverage** of already-supported libraries by targeting uncovered call sites; (6) **post-generation repair** of the metadata produced by a previous run ([`fix_post_generation_pi.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_post_generation_pi.py), [`fix_metadata_codex.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_metadata_codex.py)). Each task runs Gradle tasks against a worktree of this repo, appends a schema-validated metrics record, and — when invoked through [`forge/git_scripts/make_pr_*.py`](../forge/git_scripts/) — opens a PR for human review. See [forge/docs/architecture.md](../forge/docs/architecture.md). |\\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:46:- A `stats/<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/stats.json` mirror of per-version metrics (dynamic-access call sites, coverage, lines of code, dependency information).\\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:55:- Coverage collection (JaCoCo) and dynamic-access reporting per coordinate.\\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:74:- `latest/badges.json` — badges shown in the README (libraries supported, tested versions, dynamic-access coverage, tested LOC).\\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:84:1. **Add new library support** — generate a JUnit test suite, scaffold metadata, iterate until JVM-mode tests pass and dynamic-access metadata is collected.\\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:87:4. **Improve coverage** of already-supported libraries by targeting uncovered dynamic-access call sites.\\ndocs/DEVELOPING.md:329:  Output: `metadata/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/test/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1768:    \\\"\\\"\\\"Load dynamic-access coverage from the stored run metrics stats block.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1798:    \\\"\\\"\\\"Resolve the dynamic-access coverage report path for a new-library issue.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1809:        \\\"dynamic-access\\\",\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1810:        \\\"dynamic-access-coverage.json\\\",\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1815:    \\\"\\\"\\\"Load dynamic-access coverage directly from the generated report as a fallback.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1942:        \\\"Analyze the generated tests, metadata, stats, and dynamic-access report in this repository. \\\"\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1946:        \\\"- Explain briefly why dynamic-access coverage is missing or still very low.\\\\n\\\"\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1965:        f\\\"Automation completed for `{claimed_issue.issue_coordinates}`, but dynamic-access coverage remains \\\"\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1967:        \\\"This suggests the generated tests are not exercising the required dynamic-access paths well enough.\\\\n\\\\n\\\"\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1969:        \\\"- Inspect the generated tests and compare them with the dynamic-access report to find uncovered call sites.\\\\n\\\"\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:2631:            pipeline_argv.append(\\\"--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access\\\")\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:4537:        \\\"--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access\\\",\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:4540:            \\\"Forwarded to the new-library pipeline. Keeps generated tests for dynamic-access \\\"\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:4541:            \\\"strategies even when no dynamic-access coverage is added.\\\"\\nforge/utility_scripts/metrics_writer.py:75:    \\\"\\\"\\\"Return True when the dynamic-access stats entry matches the expected object shape.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\nforge/utility_scripts/dynamic_access_report.py:160:        return \\\"All dynamic-access call sites are covered.\\\"\\nforge/tests/test_dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py:35:            \\\"[dynamic-access] ===================================================================================\\\\n\\\"\\nforge/tests/test_dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py:36:            \\\"[dynamic-access] Progress after org.example.SomeClass: \\\"\\nforge/tests/test_dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py:38:            \\\"[dynamic-access] ===================================================================================\\\",\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:62:      \\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:80:      \\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:98:      \\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:116:      \\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:135:      \\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:153:      \\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:171:      \\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:189:      \\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:207:      \\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:225:      \\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:244:      \\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\